<p class="definition" data-word = 'Universal Gravitational Constant'>
    The Universal Graviational Constant is given by a capital \( G \) and is,
    under all conditions, equal to the value \( 6.67 \cdot 10^{-11} \frac{\text{m}^3}{\text{kg} \cdot \text{s}^2} \)
</p>

